The TA.js is a Nodejs server that operates as a trusted authority. It accepts two kind of requests:
- GET /genKey : must include "name"(String < 20 char) = the name of the user that is asking for a key, "attributes"(String) = a comma separated list of the attributes of the user to include in the key. It returns a JSON with three keys: "id" = the id of the user, "private_key" = hexadecimal charcaters that composes the private key, "pub_key" = hexadecimal charcaters that composes the public key.

- GET /getParam : it returns a plain/text of hexadecimal charcaters that composes the public key.